summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 30380, entitled: "An ordinance providing for the laying off, opening, widening, extending and establishing of the south line of Section 28, Township 24 North, Range 4 East, W.M., to a point three hundred eight (208) feet, more or less, northerly therefrom, all in the City of Seattle, providing for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor, and providing that the cost of said improvement", passed by the City Council the 18th day of November, 1912, and approved the 26th day of November, 1912; and authorizing the dismissal of the action in the Superior Court of King County, Washington, based upon said ordinances and authorizing the payment of all taxable costs.
